1
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:42,060
=The Hidden Truth=

2
00:00:42,060 --> 00:00:44,700
=Episode 2=

3
00:01:01,020 --> 00:01:02,340
(Suspect Profile: Liu Yan)

4
00:01:15,150 --> 00:01:15,990
Master.

5
00:01:17,710 --> 00:01:21,310
You already had Liu Yan's info.

6
00:01:22,510 --> 00:01:23,590
Why didn't you tell me?

7
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,430
Are you the captain?

8
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,310
Do I have to report to you?

9
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:28,760
You're my captain.

10
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,640
You're my master.

11
00:01:30,870 --> 00:01:31,920
I'm your partner.

12
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,150
You hid it from me on purpose

13
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:36,350
just to pin me to the dog theft case, right?

14
00:01:36,790 --> 00:01:38,090
You don't want me in this case.

15
00:01:39,070 --> 00:01:40,950
The dog theft case has huge social impact.

16
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,790
How is that not a major case?

17
00:01:52,430 --> 00:01:55,200
Master, Liu Yan's case is a homicide.

18
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,510
I can't ignore it.

19
00:01:56,870 --> 00:01:58,840
She was clearly poisoned.

20
00:01:59,510 --> 00:02:00,920
Her background is special.

21
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,760
Maybe it's tied

22
00:02:01,770 --> 00:02:04,520
to the Nude Banquet Case 15 years ago.

23
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,040
You say it's tied, so it is?

24
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:08,120
There's zero evidence

25
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,470
linking the two cases.

26
00:02:11,310 --> 00:02:12,840
Don't let your ego run wild

27
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,710
or force connections.

28
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:21,710
I force it?

29
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,630
You even hid

30
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:25,750
her info from me.

31
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:27,870
What choice did I have?

32
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,080
Captain Zhao.

33
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,960
If you don't want the trouble,

34
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:32,120
I'll take it on myself.

35
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,520
Captain Zhao.

36
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:36,520
We've heard

37
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:37,750
about Liu Yan's case.

38
00:02:37,910 --> 00:02:39,710
The victim's linked to the Nude Banquet Case.

39
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:42,360
That case is currently under Team One.

40
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:44,960
We'll take over Liu Yan's case as well.

41
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:48,960
Why should you?

42
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:52,590
Did you follow procedure and file a report?

43
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:54,870
We'll file it.

44
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,080
We still need

45
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,190
to add some details.

46
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,120
Once it's done,

47
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,520
I'll have Liu send it over.

48
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:02,960
Thank you, Captain Zhao.

49
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:12,470
Master,

50
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:17,280
you just let them

51
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,360
take the case?

52
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,080
Wasting your life for 15 years.

53
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,240
What did you say?

54
00:03:31,310 --> 00:03:33,560
I said, you've been slacking for 15 years.

55
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:35,270
I heard about it.

56
00:03:35,570 --> 00:03:36,870
After the Nude Banquet Case,

57
00:03:36,870 --> 00:03:37,910
you became like this.

58
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:41,680
If you fall, get back up.

59
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,430
That's what you taught me.

60
00:03:43,430 --> 00:03:44,270
But

61
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:46,030
you fell and just stayed down.

62
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,430
I don't want to deal

63
00:03:48,430 --> 00:03:49,590
with petty cases anymore.

64
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,870
I've followed you for years.

65
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:52,910
I just want to work major cases.

66
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:01,840
I held you back, huh?

67
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,520
Come.

68
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:16,390
You think only homicides matter.

69
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:18,350
That cracking one is what gives you face.

70
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:20,620
Everyone's waiting

71
00:04:20,630 --> 00:04:22,480
for those dog thieves to be caught.

72
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:25,240
You think that doesn't matter?

73
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,560
Go explain it to them yourself.

74
00:04:42,310 --> 00:04:43,510
Thanks for the like, Xiaohu.

75
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:44,600
Thank you.

76
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:49,240
Thanks for the gift, Xiaohu.

77
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,680
- Thanks, boss.
- You're welcome.

78
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,870
Love you, Xiaohu.

79
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:52,750
Love you too.

80
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,320
Thank you.

81
00:04:54,430 --> 00:04:55,800
I love you.

82
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,190
You've been on a roll lately.

83
00:04:57,190 --> 00:04:58,040
Here every day.

84
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,040
Dropping gifts every day.

85
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,870
Bro, send me 500 yuan.

86
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:01,710
I'm short.

87
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:03,720
What do you need that much for?

88
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,080
Bro.

89
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:11,670
Bro.

90
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:13,110
Bro.

91
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:15,590
Look.

92
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:17,590
Look.

93
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,110
Do we look good together?

94
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:21,690
Do we look like a couple?

95
00:05:22,810 --> 00:05:24,130
Look how many people are watching.

96
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:25,310
She says she loves me.

97
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:27,110
(Tips)
I think she means it.

98
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:30,270
You think you two match?

99
00:05:31,510 --> 00:05:33,240
What's wrong with you?

100
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:36,950
We stake out day and night,

101
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,630
steal dogs and sell them to shelters.

102
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:40,560
Then you use the money to gift a dog shelter.

103
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:42,800
Wasn't that stealing for nothing?

104
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:53,150
Bro,

105
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,320
what's wrong?

106
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,080
You feeling off?

107
00:05:57,430 --> 00:05:58,630
Bad stomach?

108
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:02,560
I told you not to eat so spicy last night.

109
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,210
Hey.

110
00:06:04,270 --> 00:06:05,160
You ordered the food.

111
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,000
Right.

112
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:07,720
Your phone. I'll leave a bad review.

113
00:06:07,870 --> 00:06:09,480
I'll scare him straight.

114
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:12,670
Xiaohu.

115
00:06:14,740 --> 00:06:15,880
I'm thinking about your mom.

116
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:29,880
Bro.

117
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:35,630
I know these years haven't been easy.

118
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,640
Look.

119
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:41,800
Delivery jobs.

120
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,630
Too many bad reviews.

121
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:47,070
Internet cafes.

122
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:48,270
Pay was trash.

123
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,320
Finally,

124
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,240
we found

125
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:56,720
the right path of dog theft.

126
00:06:58,190 --> 00:06:59,190
Big money's

127
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,600
right in front of us.

128
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:05,240
I know how hard it's been.

129
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,070
I really do.

130
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:08,840
But,

131
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,630
one thing I don't get.

132
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,430
Why think of my mom?

133
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:18,160
I just wonder

134
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,560
how she gave birth to a jerk like you.

135
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,760
I...

136
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,360
How did she give birth to you?

137
00:07:26,210 --> 00:07:27,080
Bro, come on.

138
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:27,960
Stop donating!

139
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:31,940
(Bagong Dog Shelter)

140
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:36,480
Girl, you're really smart.

141
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:38,750
These days, you gotta raise a dog.

142
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:39,910
Look.

143
00:07:39,990 --> 00:07:40,920
Other than our parents,

144
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:42,680
who truly cares about you?

145
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,190
Who only has eyes for you?

146
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,800
Who waits for you every day?

147
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,120
Who's loyal to you with no doubt?

148
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:48,600
It's dogs.

149
00:07:49,950 --> 00:07:51,120
Dating these days?

150
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,580
You're better off having a dog.

151
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:54,110
Right?

152
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:55,870
If men were reliable,

153
00:07:55,870 --> 00:07:56,950
dogs would climb trees.

154
00:07:58,390 --> 00:08:01,430
Your dogs are vaccinated, right?

155
00:08:01,430 --> 00:08:02,360
With inspection papers?

156
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:03,430
Of course.

157
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,870
At Bagong Dog Shelter,

158
00:08:04,870 --> 00:08:07,560
we're safe, legit, and reliable.

159
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:09,310
No sick dogs.

160
00:08:09,310 --> 00:08:10,190
Rest assured.

161
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:11,150
I guarantee it.

162
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:12,110
Good.

163
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:26,740
(Poisoned to Death: August 3)

164
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:29,180
(Dog-Theft Case Evidence: Sausage)

165
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:31,860
(Liu Yan Poisoning Case)

166
00:08:39,910 --> 00:08:41,440
Nude Banquet Case suspect.

167
00:08:47,150 --> 00:08:48,240
She's released.

168
00:09:06,910 --> 00:09:08,440
What breed are you looking for?

169
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:11,000
I don't really know breeds.

170
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,550
I just want to see for myself.

171
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:13,750
Find one that feels right.

172
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:14,840
Well,

173
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:16,320
let me pick one for you.

174
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,700
The one that fits your vibe.

175
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:18,730
Sure.

176
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:19,590
Alright, wait here.

177
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:22,040
I'll go pick one for you.

178
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,960
What are you doing here?

179
00:10:10,390 --> 00:10:11,480
I've picked one for you.

180
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,360
Come take a look.

181
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,720
I don't like this kind.

182
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:15,000
This one's a Pomeranian.

183
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,960
Girls get prettier raising Poms.

184
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:19,440
Three months old. Easy to raise.

185
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,160
I like that one.

186
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:24,750
Didn't expect that.

187
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,550
You're into aggressive breeds.

188
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,360
With dog thieves so bad lately,

189
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,910
they won't dare touch this one.

190
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,910
Tang Tang, what are you doing?

191
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:46,120
Why are you rushing?

192
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,440
Sorry, Mr. Qin.

193
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,630
Couldn't stop in time.

194
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:54,750
Doesn't your wife cook for you every day?

195
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,200
Why instant noodles today?

196
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,870
Because of you.

197
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,720
I got home too late last night.

198
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,080
Missed my noodles.

199
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:04,870
My wife got mad.

200
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,280
My bad.

201
00:11:08,270 --> 00:11:10,360
That's on me.

202
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,560
Mr. Qin,

203
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,550
I need another favor.

204
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,870
Just a small one.

205
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:21,270
Can you pull

206
00:11:21,270 --> 00:11:23,440
the Nude Banquet Case files?

207
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,600
Let me take a look.

208
00:11:25,030 --> 00:11:27,390
So you're planning
to work behind your master's back?

209
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:30,320
You just won't let this go?

210
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:33,200
Don't say it like that.

211
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,360
I'm not going solo.

212
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:35,470
Okay?

213
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,390
I can't give you the files.

214
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:41,680
But

215
00:11:43,910 --> 00:11:47,000
some details just came back to me.

216
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:49,200
I will confess.

217
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:52,840
Bai was already dead.

218
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,390
A... A...

219
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,240
A stick this thick...

220
00:11:56,910 --> 00:11:58,320
Two hits to the head.

221
00:11:59,150 --> 00:12:00,480
He dropped on the spot.

222
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,630
I was terrified.

223
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:04,200
I didn't even

224
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,510
see who did it

225
00:12:05,510 --> 00:12:06,630
and I ran.

226
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,240
But I'm sure

227
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:11,550
Bai was beaten to death.

228
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:16,910
Liu Yan was tough.

229
00:12:16,910 --> 00:12:18,790
She resisted the whole time.

230
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:20,440
After several interrogators,

231
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,480
she still wouldn't talk.

232
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:25,550
In the end, your master stepped in

233
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,120
under pressure

234
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:29,030
and got her confession.

235
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:31,150
In that case,

236
00:12:31,510 --> 00:12:35,270
my master knew her well.

237
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,840
He worked hard

238
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,840
to get that statement.

239
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:44,440
Now Liu Yan's dead,

240
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,150
and he doesn't react at all.

241
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:49,870
Something's off.

242
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:53,080
Maybe your master isn't wrong.

243
00:12:53,510 --> 00:12:56,320
Your theory on the cases

244
00:12:56,630 --> 00:12:58,150
is still just a guess.

245
00:12:58,270 --> 00:13:00,670
And the case is with Team One now.

246
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,120
Letting them handle it makes sense.

247
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,720
I know what to do.

248
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:17,870
We have to support each other.

249
00:13:18,030 --> 00:13:18,870
I'll head back.

250
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:23,630
Where to?

251
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:26,840
To see the Chief.

252
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,480
Get the case back.

253
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:30,390
You're not done, are you?

254
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:32,300
You really have to push it?

255
00:13:32,630 --> 00:13:33,840
I'm not pushing.

256
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:37,030
We've already started working this case.

257
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:38,360
We've put in real effort.

258
00:13:38,630 --> 00:13:40,100
I won't just hand it to Team One.

259
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:42,790
Every problem, you run to the chief.

260
00:13:43,270 --> 00:13:44,670
Forgot police discipline?

261
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:46,350
Go back.

262
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:47,670
You want to talk discipline?

263
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,720
You lecture me on this and that.

264
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,630
Then talk about this.

265
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:54,750
You interrogated Liu Yan back then.

266
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,840
She was tied to the Nude Banquet Case.

267
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:01,440
You got her confession.

268
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,960
Isn't that a little too coincidental?

269
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:07,910
No matter what,

270
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:10,390
you are not going to the Chief.

271
00:14:10,630 --> 00:14:11,600
That's overstepping.

272
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,720
Then I'm overstepping.

273
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:15,390
They buried this case years ago.

274
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,270
Now new links show up,

275
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,000
and we ignore it again?

276
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,040
Is that right?

277
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,360
You're retiring.

278
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,720
Not retired yet.

279
00:14:23,870 --> 00:14:25,270
You're still wearing the badge.

280
00:14:25,790 --> 00:14:27,030
I'm getting it today.

281
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,200
You...

282
00:14:47,870 --> 00:14:49,030
I made you some chamomile tea.

283
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,200
Good for the heat.

284
00:14:57,910 --> 00:14:58,750
Not bad.

285
00:15:07,020 --> 00:15:09,300
(Unknown Number:
Meet up on Dongshan Road.)

286
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,280
What's up?

287
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:18,420
I'm heading out for a bit.

288
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:20,110
For what?

289
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:21,870
Meeting a supplier.

290
00:15:22,870 --> 00:15:23,710
Yimo,

291
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,350
don't overwork yourself.

292
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,320
Go home early.

293
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:45,680
Long time no see.

294
00:15:47,270 --> 00:15:48,480
You're still punctual.

295
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:49,920
That's good.

296
00:15:58,670 --> 00:16:00,030
Please transfer

297
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,150
the Nude Banquet Case to Team Two.

298
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,480
Several cold cases are already with Team One.

299
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:05,770
Their workload's too heavy.

300
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:07,670
We should help share the burden.

301
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:09,840
Liu Yan's case

302
00:16:10,030 --> 00:16:11,030
was first handled by us.

303
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:13,630
There's a possibility she was poisoned.

304
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:16,360
She's also an ex-con

305
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:18,120
from the Naked Banquet Case 15 years ago.

306
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,670
The two cases may be linked.

307
00:16:21,270 --> 00:16:22,110
So I believe

308
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:23,840
we should handle the Nude Banquet Case

309
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,150
and consider consolidating the cases.

310
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,630
Your master sent you?

311
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,440
No.

312
00:16:33,390 --> 00:16:34,230
He didn't agree.

313
00:16:34,790 --> 00:16:35,720
He's close to retirement

314
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:38,240
and has other thoughts about assignments.

315
00:16:38,630 --> 00:16:40,140
But I'm willing to take responsibility.

316
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:41,560
What?

317
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:42,750
So in your eyes,

318
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,600
your master is someone who avoids hard cases?

319
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:50,550
That's not what I meant, Chief.

320
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,550
He's not that kind of person.

321
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:56,920
Why did I

322
00:16:57,650 --> 00:16:58,900
single him out at the meeting?

323
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,200
Back then,

324
00:17:01,510 --> 00:17:02,910
he poured everything into that case.

325
00:17:03,870 --> 00:17:04,880
When it was shelved,

326
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,320
it weighed on him deeply.

327
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:07,880
He never let it go.

328
00:17:08,790 --> 00:17:09,880
I just don't know

329
00:17:10,510 --> 00:17:12,270
what concerns he has this time

330
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,140
that made him stay silent.

331
00:17:16,310 --> 00:17:17,750
You're young and driven.

332
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:19,110
That's good.

333
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:23,270
But don't let your head get too big.

334
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:25,880
When he was cracking major cases,

335
00:17:26,350 --> 00:17:27,510
you hadn't even grown teeth.

336
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:30,720
Go talk to him properly.

337
00:17:31,310 --> 00:17:33,880
Find out what he's really worried about.

338
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:36,590
Understood.

339
00:17:38,550 --> 00:17:41,590
Chief, about the case...

340
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,110
Team One does have a lot

341
00:17:43,310 --> 00:17:44,240
on their plate.

342
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:48,680
You can give it a try first.

343
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,320
Thank you, Chief.

344
00:18:09,550 --> 00:18:10,390
Long time no see.

345
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:12,720
You're still punctual.

346
00:18:13,270 --> 00:18:14,110
That's good.

347
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,520
Recognize this?

348
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:27,750
You gave it to me 15 years ago.

349
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:31,830
I've kept it carefully ever since.

350
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:33,640
All these years,

351
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:36,440
I haven't forgotten

352
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:40,400
anything you gave me.

353
00:18:45,310 --> 00:18:46,310
Get to the point.

354
00:18:52,790 --> 00:18:53,630
One million.

355
00:18:55,110 --> 00:18:56,110
Once the money's in,

356
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,880
I won't take up any more of your time.

357
00:18:59,590 --> 00:19:00,510
One million?

358
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:04,320
Why?

359
00:19:07,070 --> 00:19:07,910
Why?

360
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,240
Buddy,

361
00:19:18,310 --> 00:19:19,240
I know you're busy.

362
00:19:20,350 --> 00:19:21,830
When Wang Yimo was in Xinjing,

363
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:23,550
I can look after her.

364
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:26,560
Bai,

365
00:19:27,830 --> 00:19:29,180
if you dare hurt my daughter...

366
00:19:36,070 --> 00:19:36,910
Swipe right.

367
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:42,160
Yimo's back and you didn't tell me?

368
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:44,240
She's very pretty.

369
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:46,880
A big girl now.

370
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:55,320
Bai,

371
00:19:56,830 --> 00:19:58,000
if you hurt my daughter,

372
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,590
I'll turn myself in.

373
00:20:05,030 --> 00:20:06,720
You'll have to go down with me.

374
00:20:10,790 --> 00:20:11,630
Fine.

375
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:13,840
Anyway,

376
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:16,790
I've already died once,

377
00:20:19,590 --> 00:20:20,430
haven't I?

378
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,790
If Caicai and I don't make it back today,

379
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:32,080
take care

380
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:34,910
of Wang Yimo.

381
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:23,540
(Master)

382
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:26,750
What's this old man up to?

383
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:29,680
Liu Yan was released five years ago.

384
00:21:30,110 --> 00:21:31,510
I didn't like her much.

385
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:33,410
But since we were from the same town,

386
00:21:33,640 --> 00:21:35,350
we'd chat sometimes.

387
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,110
Once she met me, all excited,

388
00:21:37,550 --> 00:21:39,440
said she was about to have money.

389
00:21:39,830 --> 00:21:41,310
She was so smug.

390
00:21:42,550 --> 00:21:43,390
What money?

391
00:21:43,630 --> 00:21:44,870
Did she say who it was?

392
00:21:45,350 --> 00:21:46,480
She didn't say much.

393
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:50,510
Just mentioned someone from the past.

394
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:52,880
I didn't press her.

395
00:21:58,680 --> 00:21:59,790
Five years out of prison.

396
00:22:04,310 --> 00:22:05,750
Why silence her now?

397
00:22:13,110 --> 00:22:13,960
Maodou.

398
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:19,950
Officer Tang.

399
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,160
You didn't forget my name, did you?

400
00:22:28,830 --> 00:22:30,920
Aren't cops supposed to have good memories?

401
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:35,200
My name's Wang Yimo.

402
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:36,160
Don't forget it.

403
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:38,640
Okay. Wang Yimo.

404
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:39,590
Got it.

405
00:22:40,070 --> 00:22:42,110
You here checking

406
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:43,680
on the dog thief again?

407
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,750
I was passing by.

408
00:22:47,750 --> 00:22:48,790
Stopped to eat.

409
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,240
Do you live nearby?

410
00:22:51,110 --> 00:22:52,960
Our old place is in this neighborhood.

411
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:53,960
I came to walk the dog.

412
00:22:54,350 --> 00:22:55,210
New one?

413
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:56,080
Yeah.

414
00:22:56,510 --> 00:22:57,590
Just got it a few days ago.

415
00:22:57,750 --> 00:22:59,030
My dad's not used to it.

416
00:22:59,310 --> 00:23:01,000
If it barks at night, he can't sleep.

417
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,110
I was thinking of leaving it

418
00:23:03,310 --> 00:23:04,790
with my bestie for a few days,

419
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:05,880
but she's allergic.

420
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:08,440
So I keep it at the old house

421
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,590
and come walk it every day.

422
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:12,640
This area's had a lot of dog thefts.

423
00:23:12,950 --> 00:23:13,790
Not safe at night.

424
00:23:13,790 --> 00:23:14,680
I'll walk you back.

425
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,040
Okay.

426
00:23:16,170 --> 00:23:17,220
Can I take the leash?

427
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:18,320
Sure.

428
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,310
Let's go, Maodou.

429
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:25,590
Why did you move away

430
00:23:25,590 --> 00:23:26,590
if you used to live here?

431
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,200
For middle school.

432
00:23:28,550 --> 00:23:30,110
My dad used the restaurant money

433
00:23:30,110 --> 00:23:31,540
to buy a school-district place.

434
00:23:32,030 --> 00:23:33,680
Your parents planned well.

435
00:23:35,310 --> 00:23:36,400
My mom passed away

436
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:38,720
when I was little.

437
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:40,680
It's just my dad and me.

438
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:42,760
I'm sorry.

439
00:23:43,070 --> 00:23:45,030
It's fine. I barely remember her.

440
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:48,880
So you went to elementary school nearby too?

441
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:51,590
Right there. Huacai Elementary.

442
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:55,190
Officer Tang,

443
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,960
are you interrogating me?

444
00:23:58,920 --> 00:24:00,000
Just casual questions.

445
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,110
Don't overthink it.

446
00:24:02,110 --> 00:24:03,310
But honestly,

447
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:07,400
you look really familiar to me.

448
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:11,160
Then I'd better be careful.

449
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:13,160
What if

450
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:15,680
you saw me on a wanted poster?

451
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:28,110
Baozi's ready.

452
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:30,750
Just me, Mr. Li.

453
00:24:31,310 --> 00:24:32,150
Where's Zhao?

454
00:24:34,110 --> 00:24:34,950
Busy.

455
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:37,440
You look upset.

456
00:24:37,920 --> 00:24:38,760
Had a fight?

457
00:24:59,220 --> 00:25:02,540
(Bagong Dog Shelter)

458
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:34,240
Your brain's rebooting?

459
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:44,720
Bro.

460
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:46,400
I have an idea.

461
00:25:48,510 --> 00:25:49,830
That brand-new brain of yours

462
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:51,400
finally working?

463
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:53,720
Say it.

464
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,550
See that building up ahead?

465
00:26:00,790 --> 00:26:01,680
The brown one?

466
00:26:02,750 --> 00:26:03,590
No.

467
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,720
The one with all glass.

468
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:11,510
That gray one, right?

469
00:26:13,310 --> 00:26:14,150
So?

470
00:26:14,350 --> 00:26:15,790
If that building were mine,

471
00:26:16,590 --> 00:26:17,830
I'd give you one unit.

472
00:26:18,790 --> 00:26:19,920
The biggest one.

473
00:26:22,350 --> 00:26:23,350
Just one?

474
00:26:24,070 --> 00:26:25,440
You ungrateful brat.

475
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:27,350
It's all yours and you only give me one?

476
00:26:27,830 --> 00:26:28,690
How could you...

477
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:29,560
I'm telling you,

478
00:26:30,030 --> 00:26:30,870
with your kind,

479
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,550
when I'm rich, you won't get a cent.

480
00:26:33,790 --> 00:26:34,630
Hello?

481
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:38,000
Yes.

482
00:26:40,590 --> 00:26:41,680
Bro, you called.

483
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,160
Got a job for me or what?

484
00:26:44,020 --> 00:26:46,140
(Bagong Dog Shelter)

485
00:26:49,820 --> 00:26:52,500
(Bagong Dog Shelter)

486
00:26:53,030 --> 00:26:55,440
Sir, what kind of dog are you looking for?

487
00:26:57,070 --> 00:26:58,440
I want the kind

488
00:27:00,590 --> 00:27:02,680
that's obedient and easy to take care of.

489
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:05,440
Alright, take a look.

490
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:13,640
I think this one looks good.

491
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,200
Can you feed it?

492
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,590
I wanna check its teeth, appetite,

493
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:21,000
see how lively it is.

494
00:27:21,350 --> 00:27:22,190
Sure.

495
00:27:23,510 --> 00:27:24,350
No dog food.

496
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:26,000
Just sausage.

497
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:27,830
I can't handle anything fancy.

498
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,590
Alright, I'll grab some.

499
00:27:29,590 --> 00:27:30,430
One moment.

500
00:27:39,030 --> 00:27:39,920
Sir,

501
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:41,480
how about this?

502
00:27:42,310 --> 00:27:43,750
This sausage, right?

503
00:27:46,030 --> 00:27:47,310
Yeah, yeah. Feed it.

504
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:48,320
Alright.

505
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,270
Sir, what do you think?

506
00:27:58,270 --> 00:27:59,110
Satisfied?

507
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,000
Good, good. Very satisfied.

508
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:01,840
It's nice.

509
00:28:06,070 --> 00:28:07,480
Hurry up. No one's around.

510
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:08,440
I'll keep watch.

511
00:28:10,030 --> 00:28:11,510
Can you be calm?

512
00:29:45,790 --> 00:29:49,310
Bro, we're just scaring ourselves.

513
00:29:50,070 --> 00:29:51,550
This dog's very obedient.

514
00:29:51,550 --> 00:29:52,640
One sausage and it's done.

515
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,750
Got me all pumped up.

516
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:55,240
Zip it.

517
00:29:55,510 --> 00:29:56,680
All that cold air.

518
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:57,550
You'll have the runs.

519
00:29:58,590 --> 00:30:00,060
- Sorry. Next time.
- Pull over.

520
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,520
Stop.

521
00:30:03,790 --> 00:30:04,630
Why are you running?

522
00:30:05,830 --> 00:30:06,670
(Police)
Pull over. Get off.

523
00:30:09,110 --> 00:30:09,950
Get off.

524
00:30:16,110 --> 00:30:16,950
No helmet.

525
00:30:17,170 --> 00:30:18,680
No double-riding on e-bikes.

526
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:21,430
Helmet… Uh…

527
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:23,720
Officer, we were in a rush

528
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:25,160
and forgot.

529
00:30:25,590 --> 00:30:26,750
Please don't fine us.

530
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:27,650
Life's not easy.

531
00:30:27,650 --> 00:30:28,510
Whose life is easy?

532
00:30:28,510 --> 00:30:29,350
Right.

533
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,680
It's dangerous driving. You get that?

534
00:30:31,680 --> 00:30:32,680
Yeah. I understand.

535
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:34,160
- I think...
- Got it. Got it.

536
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:35,510
Officer,

537
00:30:35,510 --> 00:30:36,480
we promise

538
00:30:36,790 --> 00:30:38,240
it won't happen again.

539
00:30:38,750 --> 00:30:40,190
- Talk's cheap.
- No, it's not.

540
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:41,080
Alright then.

541
00:30:41,510 --> 00:30:42,480
Let's make this stick.

542
00:30:45,020 --> 00:30:46,620
(Civilized Traffic, Safe Travel)

543
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:51,000
Green light.

544
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:54,040
Go.

545
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:03,240
Master.

546
00:31:03,830 --> 00:31:04,670
Captain Zhao.

547
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:06,790
Master. Master.

548
00:31:08,310 --> 00:31:09,150
You're back.

549
00:31:09,790 --> 00:31:11,090
How's the dog-theft case going?

550
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:13,880
I was just about to report.

551
00:31:14,310 --> 00:31:15,510
I've been looking

552
00:31:15,510 --> 00:31:17,480
into Liu Yan's social connections.

553
00:31:18,100 --> 00:31:20,010
I told you to stick
with the dog theft case.

554
00:31:20,270 --> 00:31:21,650
Why are you digging into Liu Yan?

555
00:31:22,550 --> 00:31:25,440
Isn't her case back with us now?

556
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:26,480
I have to look into it.

557
00:31:27,070 --> 00:31:27,910
Captain Zhao,

558
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,640
the precincts sent over

559
00:31:29,640 --> 00:31:31,030
recent dog theft reports.

560
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:32,160
Some of them

561
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:34,310
match the serial theft MO.

562
00:31:34,550 --> 00:31:35,790
They want us to screen them.

563
00:31:37,110 --> 00:31:38,680
The dog-theft case isn't settled yet,

564
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:40,200
and you're all in on Liu Yan.

565
00:31:40,750 --> 00:31:42,310
Who's handling the dogs and the owners?

566
00:31:45,070 --> 00:31:45,910
Give them all to him.

567
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:47,000
Finish sorting today.

568
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:49,240
Same rule as always.

569
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:50,960
Catch the dog thief first.

570
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:53,400
Stop thinking about Liu Yan.

571
00:31:57,160 --> 00:31:58,000
Let's go.

572
00:32:15,270 --> 00:32:16,110
Just poop.

573
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:19,720
We've done like 100 laps.

574
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:22,750
Go, go, go.

575
00:32:23,550 --> 00:32:24,590
Before you recognize here.

576
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:25,720
Bro,

577
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,590
I can't take this anymore.

578
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:29,880
This dog poops nonstop.

579
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,790
I'm tossing dog crap all day.

580
00:32:31,790 --> 00:32:32,920
I've lost kilos.

581
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:35,440
It doesn't just poop. It eats like crazy.

582
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:37,720
Its food bill's almost ours.

583
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:41,000
Hurry. Take this.

584
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:48,800
Hello.

585
00:32:50,790 --> 00:32:51,630
The dog's here.

586
00:32:55,590 --> 00:32:56,550
Why so rushed?

587
00:32:57,030 --> 00:32:59,510
Alright. We'll do it your way.

588
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:06,280
What's he saying?

589
00:33:07,030 --> 00:33:10,440
He's pushing us to sell the dog.

590
00:33:11,270 --> 00:33:14,240
And specifically to Bagong Dog Shelter.

591
00:33:15,310 --> 00:33:16,400
No way.

592
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:18,550
Bagong pays too little.

593
00:33:18,830 --> 00:33:21,240
But he said it has to be Bagong.

594
00:33:21,550 --> 00:33:22,590
That's weird.

595
00:33:23,110 --> 00:33:24,830
He never cared who I sold to before.

596
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,550
Now it's gotta be Bagong.

597
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:28,800
Do you think

598
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:31,200
they might be working together?

599
00:33:32,070 --> 00:33:33,720
Nah. Doesn't seem like it.

600
00:33:34,030 --> 00:33:35,400
He seems alright.

601
00:33:57,790 --> 00:33:59,440
Tang Tang, it's past mealtime.

602
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:00,440
Let's go grab a bite.

603
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:02,350
I'm not hungry. You guys go.

604
00:34:03,550 --> 00:34:04,390
Liu, Li,

605
00:34:04,640 --> 00:34:05,480
let's go eat.

606
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:07,720
Yeah, let's go.

607
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:10,640
Not coming?

608
00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:12,480
Enjoy.

609
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:13,800
Don't worry about me.

610
00:34:35,020 --> 00:34:37,900
(Lost: Aug 3)

611
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:39,100
(Poisoned Sausage Found: Aug 23)

612
00:34:42,860 --> 00:34:44,820
(Poisoned to Death: Jul 20)

613
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:46,550
In that case,

614
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:48,070
my master

615
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:50,550
knew her well.

616
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:52,960
Now Liu Yan's dead,

617
00:34:54,110 --> 00:34:55,550
and he doesn't react at all.

618
00:35:02,660 --> 00:35:05,140
(Poisoned Sausage Found: Aug 23;
Yili Yangguang Teahouse)

619
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:11,110
That's what he's been looking into.

620
00:35:14,580 --> 00:35:16,380
(Master)

621
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:53,550
Your nose is getting sharp.

622
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:55,390
Followed the scent here?

623
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:56,300
Of course.

624
00:35:56,360 --> 00:35:57,920
How'd you know I made dumplings today?

625
00:35:58,030 --> 00:35:59,110
I smelled it at the office.

626
00:35:59,190 --> 00:36:01,230
So I rushed all the way over.

627
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:03,280
Wash your hands.

628
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:23,680
I'm taking it, okay?

629
00:36:24,150 --> 00:36:24,990
Dig in.

630
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:33,680
Master,

631
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:36,110
what have you been busy with lately?

632
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,880
Feels like you're avoiding me.

633
00:36:39,550 --> 00:36:40,670
What are you talking about?

634
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:42,510
I've been working a case.

635
00:36:44,190 --> 00:36:45,030
Let me guess.

636
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:46,550
Liu Yan's case?

637
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:47,760
You went without me.

638
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:48,600
You hid it from me.

639
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:49,960
Going solo's not nice.

640
00:36:50,550 --> 00:36:52,360
I told you to focus on the dog theft case.

641
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:53,640
Instead,

642
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:56,230
you latched onto Liu Yan's connections

643
00:36:56,230 --> 00:36:57,150
and chased it.

644
00:36:57,710 --> 00:36:59,550
Poisoning is just a theory.

645
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,710
Don't fit the facts to your theory.

646
00:37:03,110 --> 00:37:05,480
I had to check the sausage myself.

647
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,110
Trying to get you to listen

648
00:37:07,590 --> 00:37:08,960
is like I'm hurting you.

649
00:37:09,630 --> 00:37:10,590
Master,

650
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,760
I came to apologize.

651
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:13,760
I'm sorry.

652
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:16,110
Don't investigate alone without me.

653
00:37:16,590 --> 00:37:17,710
I'll listen from now on.

654
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:19,880
I was worried

655
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:21,280
you had things bottled up.

656
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:23,070
For anyone who like aggressive breeds,

657
00:37:23,070 --> 00:37:25,000
I recommend a Malinois.

658
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:26,630
Look at that coat.

659
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:28,710
Watching dog shelter livestreams?

660
00:37:29,110 --> 00:37:29,950
Suspicious of them?

661
00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:33,550
This phone screen

662
00:37:34,670 --> 00:37:35,760
is this small.

663
00:37:36,230 --> 00:37:37,070
What you see

664
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:39,110
is what they want you to see.

665
00:37:40,150 --> 00:37:41,190
That shelter

666
00:37:41,630 --> 00:37:42,480
look lively,

667
00:37:42,710 --> 00:37:44,140
keeps bragging about how legit it is,

668
00:37:44,590 --> 00:37:47,280
calling everyone "loved ones."

669
00:37:47,390 --> 00:37:48,320
But behind the scenes,

670
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,190
you have no idea who's involved.

671
00:37:51,070 --> 00:37:51,920
You don't know...

672
00:37:52,070 --> 00:37:53,360
A Malinois is a real showstopper.

673
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:54,200
That's my dog.

674
00:37:54,710 --> 00:37:55,630
You stole my dog.

675
00:37:57,320 --> 00:37:58,160
Miss.

676
00:38:01,710 --> 00:38:02,800
This is my dog.

677
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:03,880
You stole it.

678
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:04,960
You got it wrong.

679
00:38:04,970 --> 00:38:05,830
Maodou.

680
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:08,440
Is she the girl at the farmers' market?

681
00:38:09,540 --> 00:38:10,390
Is she...

682
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:11,240
Maodou.

683
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:12,710
Maodou, run!

684
00:38:12,710 --> 00:38:13,550
Is it her?

685
00:38:16,300 --> 00:38:18,020
(Yimo: Maodou's taken! Shelter!
Dog thieves are here! Help me!)

686
00:38:21,790 --> 00:38:27,280
♪Dreams of the past sleep in the chill♪

687
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:30,730
♪Now I run toward the light♪

688
00:38:32,580 --> 00:38:37,840
♪What does the fire burn,
what does it reveal?♪

689
00:38:38,160 --> 00:38:41,810
♪Is the answer found when the sun rises♪

690
00:38:42,420 --> 00:38:46,710
♪If it's all a lie♪

691
00:38:47,900 --> 00:38:52,070
♪Should I tear it open?♪

692
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:58,120
♪If it's all part of the journey♪

693
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:03,650
♪Then face the blaze head-on♪

694
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:08,510
♪Let the sun awaken my heart's crave♪

695
00:39:09,050 --> 00:39:14,780
♪Pain reminds me I'm alive♪

696
00:39:14,900 --> 00:39:19,710
♪The world can't take away every clear sky♪

697
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:25,510
♪The hotter it gets, the fiercer I fight♪

698
00:39:25,820 --> 00:39:30,540
♪Let the sun burn away all I lean upon♪

699
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:36,540
♪Leave me only what endures♪

700
00:39:36,650 --> 00:39:42,200
♪At the cliff's edge, all fear shatters♪

701
00:39:42,260 --> 00:39:49,210
♪With a grounded heart, a soul like fire♪
